##The second week back to work, the reporter visited the Shanghai subway bus taxi, the city's Public Transport Safety?

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

To Stop the spread of pneumonia caused by COVID-19, disinfection of public transport is particularly important.

Reporter | Liu Zhaohui

Today marks the start of the second week of work in Shanghai after the Spring Festival holiday. Since the resumption of work on February 10, many people have returned to work, while more and more people are returning to Shanghai, and the flow of public transport in Shanghai will become more and more intense. In the current epidemic prevention and control work in Shanghai is still in a period of tension, choose public transport travel to and from work is not safe, is a lot of people in the heart of the question.

To Stop the spread of pneumonia caused by COVID-19, disinfection of public transport is particularly important. According to the on-the-spot visit of the reporter and the information obtained from the three major industries of subway, bus and taxi, the Shanghai Public Transportation Industry has made a strict deployment of the epidemic prevention and control, and the prevention and control work and disinfection measures have been further strengthened.

Subway: temperature network coverage

At 8:00 a.m. , the reporter saw that a temperature measurement point was set up outside the Shanghai Railway Station on line 3. Subway workers in full body protective clothing stood ready to take strict temperature measurements on every passenger entering the station. According to the requirements of the city's prevention and control work, once passengers with temperature measurement exceeding 37.3 °C are found, they will immediately call the duty stationmaster, register and report the personal information of the passengers, and implement classified control, and transfer passengers to the quarantine area for body temperature review, review and dial 120 to the scene for investigation.

It is understood that temperature measurements are carried out outside the Shanghai Railway Station on Line 1, the Shanghai South Railway Station, the Shanghai Railway Station on Line 3, the Shanghai South Railway Station and the subway. The station adopts one-way traffic by adjusting part of the entrances and exits, try to avoid the gathering of passengers indoors.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Workers take temperature readings of incoming passengers at Shanghai Railway Station on Line 3

In order to ensure the safety of Rail Transit passengers, from February 12, a total of 412 stations in Shanghai subway network (except for the suspension of line 11 for three stations) will be covered by temperature measurement. There are 751 temperature measuring points in the whole network, of which 224 points are used in thermal imager and 527 points are used in forehead thermometer. And with the recent return passenger flow arriving in Shanghai every day after the festival and the increasing capacity of the city's airports, railway stations and other transportation hubs, the Shanghai subway, on the basis of the original implementation of temperature measurement, by the staff wearing professional protective clothing in Rail Transit 12 portal stations to carry out temperature, for the arrival of passengers temperature screening.

At present, there are two ways to measure the temperature in Shanghai subway station, one is "hand-held non-contact thermometer" , the other is "non-cooperation thermal imaging" temperature measurement system. In stations where temperature is measured by "non-cooperative thermal imaging" , passengers do not need to stop and staff do not need to step forward to carry out temperature measurement operations. When passengers pass through the security check, they have entered the temperature measurement range synchronously, and the system has already carried out temperature measurement on personnel, the staff can get the body temperature directly through the screen. If the temperature is over the standard value, there will be a warning sound to remind the staff.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Temperature measurement system of "non-cooperation thermal imaging" in subway station

According to regulations, the station will sterilize the equipment every hour, Shanghai Metro said. Since the resumption of work on February 10, the subway has been a daily train disinfection, increased to the end of each peak back to the warehouse must be closed again disinfection. The frequency of disinfection at the station has been increased to four times a day, with an hour-by-hour cleaning of the areas closely touched by passengers. Ventilation system to take the fresh air conditions, ventilation lines and filters twice a week cleaning and disinfection. In addition, in the event of sudden illness of passengers and information on suspected or confirmed cases, thorough disinfection measures should be taken immediately.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Shanghai subway workers disinfect subway cars

During the epidemic period, the passenger flow was not large for the whole rail transit network, we also remind you to remember the five-character rule advocated by Shanghai Metro: "wear a mask the whole time, check your body temperature at the station, avoid crowd, please go wrong peak, please limit the flow. " In order to maximize the safety of subway travel.

Public Transport: Disinfection of key lines three times a day

In response to the arrival of the city's return and resumption of work passenger flow, the Shanghai public transport authorities have also strictly implemented the epidemic prevention and Control Standard operation, implemented an all-weather, all-process, all-coverage "Mitsutomo" management, while making good luck to be able to deploy, the work of disinfection and ventilation of buses and temperature measurement of passengers at hub stations has been strengthened.

The reporter learned from Jiushi bus that as the largest bus company in Shanghai, its five current bus operating companies have nearly 8,000 operating vehicles, and they carry out disinfection and cleaning at least once a day, while on 56 key routes such as route 71, three sterilizations a day have been carried out since about 10 days ago, and disinfection records have been posted at the front door of vehicles.

According to the work requirements of epidemic prevention and control, all public transport vehicles must open windows after operation to the terminal station to maintain air circulation. In addition, Jiushi bus has taken temperature measurements for passengers boarding and alighting at 79 hub stations and 273 line terminals in the city. At the same time, temporary shelters for passengers with fever have been set up at 42 closed hubs.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The public transport vehicles of the key lines shall be disinfected three times a day

Reporters found that the bus to increase the bus compartment disinfection efforts, but also in some public transport lines added a large-scale electric sprayer to promote the use of the pilot. According to reports, this "new weapon" can spray fine atomized particles of a new disinfectant, disinfection factors can be well suspended in the air, and carry out continuous and effective killing of harmful microorganisms, compared with the original manual spraying mode, it not only speeds up the disinfection speed, enhances the disinfection efficiency and Factor of safety, but also greatly improves the disinfection coverage in the vehicle, which has no pungent taste and reduces passengers'discomfort.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Public Transport personnel use large-scale electric sprayer disinfection

In addition to the spraying disinfection, the public transport workers also thoroughly sterilize and clean the key contact parts, such as door handle, handle, seat back and so on. 71 bus driver side into the introduction, the car every wipe and spray disinfection again, at least 30 minutes. He disinfects it once every morning and repeats it twice between operations, "from top to bottom, from inside to outside, " air conditioning vents, levers, bracelets, armrests, seat backs, seat surfaces, sidewalls, driving areas, card swipers, and floors, no corner is left unturned.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Bus Cars are wiped clean. No loose ends

The temporary shelters for feverish passengers at bus hubs, with clearly identifiable signs and contact information of the CDC, are equipped with seats, isolation facilities and disinfection supplies and are managed by trained professionals. The temporary accommodation is located away from the area of the bus operators and at least 2 metres away from the passageway where passengers gather in order to avoid cross-infection of Febrile passengers as they pass. Jiushi bus, they set up 1200 pieces of "get on the bus, wear a mask, protect you and me, " the warm prompt signs, friendly remind passengers to do their own protection work.

It is understood that in order to strengthen the prevention and control of the epidemic situation in the city's public transport, the Jiushi public transport has refined and improved the long-term mechanism for the prevention and control of various epidemic situations, it involves working mechanism, safety protection of staff and workers, safety protection of passengers, disinfection of operating vehicles, management of epidemic prevention materials, etc. , and is divided into two levels: the Leading Group and the Inspection Brigade of the group's Safety Management Department, to Carry Out Inspection and supervision on the implementation of various prevention and control measures without interruption. At the same time, Jushi bus also actively organized hundreds of volunteers to carry out anti-epidemic volunteer service activities, to assist the field management company to enter the bus parking lot personnel, vehicles for temperature registration and personnel identification; Do a good job of inspection and supervision to the bus terminal.

TAXI: One bad time and one disinfectant

With the resumption of work in enterprises and institutions in Shanghai, passenger demand for taxis has risen. Shanghai taxi industry has also taken a variety of measures to ensure the safety of passengers.

Every taxi every day "a check-in a disinfection a report" , the car passengers easy to reach the door handle, seats and other locations, focus on wiping disinfection, to ensure that the public have a safe and clean travel environment.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Every taxi is strictly disinfected before it goes on the road

The reporter learned from the Public Rental Company, from two weeks ago, the public rental started "the most stringent safety and epidemic prevention model. ". The interior of the cab is cleaned daily with a special cleaning solution and disinfectant. Before departure, each vehicle must go through multiple disinfection "checkpoints" , by the quality inspection personnel affixed labels, before being "approved" on the road. At the same time, the public rental vehicles for each operation has been equipped with a sterilizing pot, to achieve "one difference, one disinfection" , and requires drivers in operation to maintain vehicle ventilation, "mouth cover, hand pot, strict epidemic prevention, " To ensure the health and safety of themselves and their passengers. Each branch of the motorcade has arranged the disinfectant to supply, the convenient driver has used up to make the supplement.

"We bought special disinfectant to sterilize the areas that taxi passengers and drivers may come in contact with, such as door locks, seat cushions, floor mats, back seats and steering wheels, " Volkswagen said. "I now wear a mask every day and drive. Next thing I know, I have a van full of businesses and I spray myself. " "This is a very special time, " said Yang, a driver of a Volkswagen taxi. "The company has allocated a pot of disinfectant for us. It is good for our drivers and safe for our customers. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The reporter learned that as early as before the Spring Festival, the public rental has already strengthened the management of entering and leaving the venues, and strengthened the management and protection of key areas such as office areas and vehicle fleets, focus on ensuring the disinfection and cleaning of vehicles and the driver of the temperature test work, each taxi every day "a check-in a report of disinfection. ". In the "two markets and three stations (three railway stations in Shanghai's two major airports) " , where passenger demand is high, the Volkswagen leasing quality inspection team is also fully mobilized, fully armed, to carry out "one-car-one-clean-up" for the waiting taxis, guide passengers to the sanitized vehicle.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Volkswagen lease quality inspection team disinfected vehicles in the airport waiting area

In addition, on February 13, Volkswagen travel, a ride-hailing platform under the public transportation banner, announced that it would invest an additional 1 million yuan to provide public welfare travel services for the families of the Hubei Medical Team, and will join forces with Hema, to provide free distribution and other services for the medical staff of the designated hospitals for epidemic prevention in Shanghai. The move follows the announcement on January 30 that it will spend 1 million yuan to provide free travel services to families of medical staff in Shanghai. The platform, through the Shanghai Medical Union, presents a "public welfare travel card" to the family members of each medical and nursing staff in Hubei Province, which contains 1,000 yuan of free travel tickets and VIP service for vehicle protection, alleviating the worries of front-line medical and nursing staff. So far, the first batch of "public welfare travel cards" have basically been converted. With Shanghai sending several batches of medical teams to Wuhan, the total number of medical personnel has reached nearly 1,000. The decision of the mass travel agency to invest an additional 1 million yuan, to ensure that the families of every member of the medical team are able to enjoy the free services provided by public transportation.
